{ Black continues with his development. } 13. h4 Qa5
{ Intending b4 without allowing Na4. } 14. a3
{ This ensures that the knight will stay on c3. In case of  14.Kb1  b4  15.Ne2  e5  16.Be3  d5  we can see the importance of White's control over the d5-square: without it Black easily manages to push d5 and equalises. }
