O-O { Naturally, Black castles and can then use the a-file to his advantage. }
17. Qxa7 Bc6
{ Finally activating the light-squared bishop. Now with the b7-pawn defended Black threatens to regain the pawn by taking on h2. }
18. f4 { Defending the pawn on h2 by blocking the h2-b8 diagonal. } 18... Be4
