{ White cannot take on c3 because after  14.Qxc3?  Nxe4  Black will take  on f2 next and regain the exchange leaving him with a winning position as he will be two pawns up. }
14... Rc7
{ The rook retreats to c7 to defend the bishop on d7 in case White takes on e5 and opens the d-file. }
15. Bg5 Bb5
{ A good move, the exchange of the light-squared bishop will secure the c4-square for the knight. }
