13. Be3 Qc6 { Black moves the queen to c6 in order to attack the e4-pawn. } 14.
f4 Nc4 { The only sensible option, Black obtains the bishop pair now. } 15.
Bxc4 Qxc4
{ The position is dynamically balanced. Black's chances are rather good - he has a stable position and the bishop pair. A sample line is: }
16. Bd4 b5 { Threatening b4 when the e4-pawn will have no protection. } 17. e5
{ White breaks through the centre. } 17... Nd5
{ Black shouldn't open the d-file by taking on e5 because White is ready to use it to his advantage. }
18. Nxd5 exd5
{ The correct, if surprising, capture. The idea is to open the h3-c8 diagonal for the light-squared bishop so it can go to f5 to put pressure on the pawn on c2. Black has excellent play here and White needs to be careful. }
