{ It is also possible to castle first, the only difference lies in the line with an immediate g4, but against both  7...Nc6  8.g4  and @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/pp2bppp/3ppn2/8/3NP3/2N1BP2/PPP3PP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  7...O-O  8.g4  Black is fine. Here is a sample line against the latter:  8...d5!  9.e5  Ne8  10.Qd2  Nc6  with good counterplay in the centre. In case of @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/pp2bppp/3ppn2/8/3NP3/2N1BP2/PPP3PP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  7...O-O  8.Qd2  Nc6  we have a transposition to7...Nc6 8.Qd2 O-O. }
