{ By attacking the rook on d1 Black alleviates the pressure on the d-file. }
16. Be2 Bxe3
{ Luring the queen to the e-file so that the rook can gain a tempo with Re8. }
17. Qxe3 Re8
{ Black's activity and the weakness of the pawn on f4 compensate for the IQP on d5. }
18. Qd2 Bxe2 { The bishop was hanging to Black continues with tempo. } 19. Nxe2
Qd6 { Putting more pressure on the pawn on f4. } 20. f5 Rad8
{ Black is just in time to defend the pawn on d5. Black has good chances in this complex position. The pawns on g5 and f5 are over-extended and can become weak. Another idea is for the rook on the e-file to come to e4 to control the 4th rank and allow for Nf4. }
