18. Bxd5 Rad8 { Pinning the bishop and activating the rook. } 19. c4 b6
{ Another important move for Black. He removes the pawn from the light square and also defends the pawn on a7. Without targets, the bishop on d5 is useless. Now Black wants to put a knight on f4 and then either take the bishop or start moving his kingside majority with h5-h4. The exchange of queens is also acceptable for Black as then he can advance his kingside structure more easily, especially with the help of the king and the knight on f4. }
