16... Bxe3 { Both Black's bishops were hanging, so Black had to take on e3. }
17. Qxd7 Qc8
{ A nice move - defending the pawn on b7 and not allowing a rook on the 7th rank after the exchange of queens. Now Black wants to continue with Nf6, chasing away the queen from d7, or Nf4, placing the knight on a dominant square. Black has a pleasant position, always with the long-term advantage of the better pawn structure. }
