14. Rxd4
{ Controlling the b4-square, at least for now. In case of  14.Bxd4  b4  Black's counterplay starts immediately. }
14... Bc6
{ Black keeps it flexible - the bishop must come to c6 in order to open the b-file, but which rook should occupy the b-file is unclear for now, so Black keeps both options open. }
