24... Bf6
{ Bringing back the bishop before playing c3, which severs the white bishop's control of the e1-square. Black is playing for a win without any risk here: he will create luft for his king and then maneuver with his pieces combining the threat of a back-rank mate with an attack on White's kingside pawns. Note that the white queen will have to stay on the first rank to defend it, meaning that White cannot create any counterplay. }
