{ The simple solution. It's possible to be more aggressive and play  13...d5!?  14.e5  Ne4  as well, as this works out nicely for Black, but it also requires more calculation @@StartBracket@@or memorisation@@EndBracket@@. }
14. g5 Nd7
{ With a comfortable position for Black. Now his main idea is the e5-push to undermine the pawn on g5 and after the exchange on f4 to obtain the e5-square for the knight. }
