Nbd7
{ Black finishes development and plans to play Rc8, threatening the typical exchange sacrifice on c3. }
11. O-O-O
{ Taking on b7 is bad,  11.Qxb7?  Rb8  followed by Rxb2 is almost winning for Black as White's king is stuck in the centre and White is also lagging in development. }
11... Rc8
{ Black threatens to take on c3. White has many options at his disposal now. }
12. Qxb7
{ This is the only decent move that allows an exchange sacrifice on c3 when White isn't worse at least. }
12... Rxc3
{ Black naturally takes on c3. If he prefers to avoid the possible repetition he can try  12...Rc7!?  13.Qb3  exf4  14.Bxf4  Nc5  with unclear play. }
13. bxc3 Qa5 { Introducing the threats of Qxc3, Qxa2 and Rb8. } 14. Qb4 Qc7
{ Not  14...Qxa2?  15.Bc4  which traps the queen. } 15. Qc4 Qa5
{ Threatening d5. White is forced to repeat moves. } 16. Qb4 Qc7
{ With a repetition. } *

