{ Developing naturally. The alternative  13...d5  is also good. } 14. Bb5
{ White tries to develop quickly. Defending the pawn with  14.Bd2?  is bad in view of  14...d5  and Black is almost winning: he will continue with e4, Rc8, Nb6 and his slow-burning attack cannot be stopped. }
14... Nb6
{ Getting the knight closer to the queenside. It can jump to c4 and Black can also play Rc8. }
