{ This is dubious. } 15... Nxd5 16. Rxd5 Nf6
{ Moving away from the attacked square and attacking the rook before picking up the pawn on f4. }
17. Rd2 Qxf4
{ Black is better here as White's pieces are clumsy and Black is threatening to play Rfd8 or simply pick up the f5-pawn. }
