[Round "?"]
[White "9. Strategy and Tactics"]
[Black "Dark Squares Strategy #1"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "2rqnrk1/3bbppp/p1npp3/1p6/4PPP1/PNN1B3/1PP3BP/R2Q1R1K b - - 0 14"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White advances on the kingside in typical Sicilian fashion. Here Black has an original way to fight for the ever-important dark squares and stop White's advance. How does he go about it? }
14... g5
{ Black wants to provoke either fxg5 or f5, which would give him access to the dream square e5 for his knight. As a rule of thumb, having an eternal knight on e5 @@StartBracket@@which cannot be chased away with a pawn@@EndBracket@@ is a guarantee for good play and a good defence against a kingside attack. }
*

