[SetUp "1"]

{ In this typical position with a pawn on e4 vs a pawn on d6, Black's play is based on the control and use of the dark squares. Black's ideal scenario is to exchange the dark-squared bishops because in that case, he will aim for a position with a good knight on e5 vs a bad bishop on e2, which is close to strategically winning. With all this in mind, can you guess Black's next move? }
11... Ne8 *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
