[White "9. Strategy and Tactics"]
[Black "Strike in the Centre #1"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqkb1r/pp3pp1/2nppn1p/8/3NP1PP/2N5/PPP2P2/R1BQKBR1 b Qkq - 0 8"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White is threatening to push away the f6-knight with g5. If forced to move the knight, Black will also have diminished control over the centre. However, Black is just in time to strike in the centre, following the classical maxim that an attack on the flank is best answered with a counter-thrust in the centre. Can you find Black's best move? }
8... d5
{ As is typical in the Modern Scheveningen, Black strikes in the centre just in time, following the classical maxim that an attack on the flank should be met by a counterstrike in the centre. }
*

