[SetUp "1"]

{ White stabilised the position in the centre and intends h4 and g5. Black doesn't waste time and starts his queenside attack immediately. How? }
13... Rxc3 14. bxc3 a6
{ It is important to understand that this exchange sacrifice gives Black the long-term advantage of the weakness of White's king. It will allow Black a slow-burning attack with ...Qa5, ...b5, ...O-O, ...Rc8 etc. In other words, Black will continue to play positionally with a clear target in mind - the white king. }
